ou feel unsafe in the property or forces you to leave. </p>\n\n<p>Harassment can include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>stopping services, like electricity</li>\n  <li>withholding keys - eg there are 2 tenants in a property but the landlord will only give 1 key</li>\n  <li>refusing to carry out repairs</li>\n  <li>anti-social behaviour by a landlord&rsquo;s agent - eg a friend of the landlord moves in next door and causes problems</li>\n  <li>threats and physical violence</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Illegal eviction and tenants&rsquo; rights</h2>\n<p>Your landlord may be guilty of illegal eviction if you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>aren’t given the notice to leave the property that your landlord must give you</li>\n  <li>find the locks have been changed</li>\n  <li>are evicted without a court order</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Even if your landlord’s property is repossessed by their mortgage lender, the lender must give you a notice period so you can find other accommodation. Citizens Advice has information on <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.adviceguide.org.uk/index/your_family/home_and_neighbourhood_index_ew/renting_a_home_index_ew/repossession_by_your_landlord_s_mortgage_lender.htm/\" title=\"Repossession by your landlord’s mortgage lender\">repossession by your landlord’s mortgage lender.</a></p>\n\n<h2>What you can do</h2>\n<p>If you think you’re being harassed or threatened with illegal eviction, or the property you rent is being repossessed, <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://legaladviserfinder.justice.gov.uk/AdviserSearch.do\" title=\"Contact a legal adviser\">contact a legal adviser</a> or Shelter’s <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://england.shelter.org.uk/get_advice/how_we_can_help/housing_advice_helpline/\" title=\"Shelter's housing advice helpline\">housing advice helpline.</a></p>\n\n<p>The Department for Communities and Local Government has a <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.communities.gov.uk/publications/housing/mylandlordwants\" title=\"My landlord wants me out\">guide for tenant